					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6739677#post-3912683</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6739677/scp-1750#post-3912683</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 15 Aug 2018 20:56:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Questionable Object</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1868560</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Not really, effectively all liquid fossil fuels is composed of plant or aquatic animal material that formed 300-400 million years ago or earlier about 100-200 million years before the early Triassic when the first (proto-)dinosaurs started to show up so the gas you put in your car'd be more likely to be possessed by a trilobite than a dinosaur.</p> <p>And there's the fact dinosaurs have more in common with birds than reptiles (birds being the descendants of a branch of the dinosaur phylum(Class? Or is it Order? Highschool Bio was a long time ago&#8230;) so the whole &quot;Reptilian ectomorphs&quot; might be a bit iffy since their reptillianity is quite arguable.</p> <p>Long story short the science is pretty stacked against this skip in my opinion, poor little thing that it is.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
